First let’s finish the thread we started: why waves, rotation, and oscillations are actually the same structure.

Rotation → Waves

If you spin a point around a circle and watch only one coordinate, you get a wave.

Interpretation:
	•	A circle is uniform rotation.
	•	Sine is the vertical projection of that rotation.
	•	Cosine is the horizontal projection.

So a sine wave is literally a shadow of circular motion.

That’s why physics everywhere uses:
	•	sine waves for sound
	•	sine waves for light
	•	sine waves for quantum wavefunctions
	•	sine waves for electrical signals

Because oscillation is just rotation viewed through one dimension.

This is exactly what Euler’s formula revealed earlier.

