An equation that links even more things

Here’s another one mathematicians consider incredibly deep.

Fourier Transform (structure of signals)

f(t)=\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} F(\omega)e^{i\omega t},d\omega

Why this equation is wild

It says:

Every signal in the universe can be built from rotating waves.

This connects:

Domain	What it explains
Music	notes and harmonics
Electrical engineering	signals and radio
Image compression	JPEG / video codecs
Quantum mechanics	wavefunctions
MRI scanners	reconstructing body images
Seismology	earthquake waves

So the universe can be decomposed into spinning exponentials e^{i\omega t}.

Which are just Euler rotations again.

