One even stranger identity

Another equation that links geometry, infinity, and number theory is:

Basel Problem

\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n^2}=\frac{\pi^2}{6}

This shocked mathematicians because:
	•	the sum of reciprocals of integers
	•	somehow equals a formula involving π (circle geometry).

So integers secretly encode circle geometry.

That’s a deep hint that discrete numbers and continuous geometry are connected.

